Context("Numeric");
#given
$v = random(3,5,.1);

#image scale
$imgScale = .2;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*1275;
$height = $imgScale*1660;

#computation
$omega = $v/0.75; # rad/s
$a_p_n = 2.5 * $omega**2; #cm/s2
$a_p_t = sqrt(150**2 - $a_p_n**2); #cm/s2
$alpha = $a_p_t / 2.5; #rad/s2
$a_B = 0.75*$alpha; #cm/s2


#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>1,
tolType=>'absolute');

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "UBC-DYN-18-003.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

Assume that a string is wrapped around a spinning top and at the moment shown, it is unravelling at a rate of [`V = [$v]`] [`cm/s`]. At the same instant, the total acceleration of point [`p`] is equal to [`150`] [`cm/s^2`]. Calculate the angular acceleration of the spinning top as well as the acceleration of the string unravelling from the spinning top. 

[`\alpha_{top}=`] [____]{$alpha} [`rad/s^2`]  
[`a_{string}=`] [____]{$a_B} [`cm/s^2`]

_Round your answers to one decimal place_.

END_PGML

